          "date": "2018-06-03 21:05:43.000000000",
          "tz": 330
        },
        "subject": "LU-11070 llite: Partial page write by NFS",
        "message": "LU-11070 llite: Partial page write by NFS\n\nWhen NFS is used above Lustre, it is seen that the write\nhas the first partial size vector which is causing all\nfollowing page size vector to be considered as partial.\nThis in tern produces read requests/rpcs and affect the\nproformance.\n\nTo avoid this problem, scan the vector and based on\npattern use the hint to avoid the read requests.\n\nBased on this thought/approach cook proto-type patch.\n\nChange-Id: Iff4c40aa837e5ea49d60a53004af27ff0d9129a1\nSigned-off-by: Rahul Deshmukh <rdeshmukh@ddn.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
